               <interp inst="t17480907-52" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17480907-52" type="year" value="1748"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17480907-52" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17480907"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17480907-52" type="date" value="17480907"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17480907-52-off267-c292" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480907-52-defend397 t17480907-52-off267 t17480907-52-verdict272"></join>
         
               <p>442. 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-defend397" type="defendantName">
                  Robert 
                  Chevin 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-defend397" type="surname" value="Chevin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-defend397" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-defend397" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t17480907-52-off267" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-off267" type="offenceCategory" value="sexual"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-off267" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bigamy"></interp>
               feloniously marrying 
                     
                        <persName id="t17480907-52-victim399" type="victimName">
                           Elizabeth 
                           Atwood 
                        <interp inst="t17480907-52-victim399" type="surname" value="Atwood"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17480907-52-victim399" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17480907-52-victim399" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , on the <rs id="t17480907-52-cd268" type="crimeDate">25th of November 1747</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480907-52-off267 t17480907-52-cd268"></join>. his former <rs id="t17480907-52-viclabel269" type="occupation">wife</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480907-52-victim401 t17480907-52-viclabel269"></join>, 
                     
                        <persName id="t17480907-52-victim401" type="victimName">
                           Anne 
                           Towns 
                        <interp inst="t17480907-52-victim401" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17480907-52-victim401" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17480907-52-victim401" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                      
                   , being then living
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17480907-52-person402">
                  James 
                  Buston 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person402" type="surname" value="Buston"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person402" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person402" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk to the deputy register of the vicar-general of the archbishop of Canterbury : this is the book of warrants for licenses, and it does appear here, that on the 12th of October 1731. 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person403">
                  Robert 
                  Chevin 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person403" type="surname" value="Chevin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person403" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person403" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of Skopwith in Lincolnshire, batchellor, appeared, and said that he did intend to marry 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person404">
                  Anne 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person404" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person404" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person404" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , spinster.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="174809070025"></xptr>[The Reverend Mr. Stanhope Elliston , Parson of St. Bennet Paul's-wharf, produced the book of marriages belonging to that parish.]</p>
               <p>Q. to Mr. Elliston. Is there any entry of a marriage on the 12th of October 1731. of Robert Chevin, of Skopwith in Lincolnshire , to Mrs. Anne Towns?</p>
               <p>Elliston. Yes; there is any entry here, that 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person405">
                  Robert 
                  Chevin 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person405" type="surname" value="Chevin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person405" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person405" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of Skopwith in Lincolnshire, batchellor, was married, the 31st of October, 1731. to 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person406">
                  Anne 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person406" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person406" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person406" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , spinster .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17480907-52-person407">
                  Matthew 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person407" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person407" type="given" value="Matthew"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner lived with my sister, as man and wife, about 12 years ; but I have not seen the prisoner these 7 years .</p>
               <p>Q. What was your sister's name?</p>
               <p>Towns. Anne Towns.</p>
               <p>Pris. Coun . Did you use to visit them?</p>
               <p>Towns. Yes ; and he acknowledged her as his wife, and she him as her husband .</p>
               <p>Pris. Coun . Is your sister, 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person408">
                  Anne 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person408" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person408" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person408" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , living now?</p>
               <p>Towns. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. When did you see her?</p>
               <p>Towns . About a fortnight ago.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17480907-52-person409">
                  John 
                  Day 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person409" type="surname" value="Day"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person409" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             . I have known the prisoner about 4 years ; he lodged at my house.</p>
               <p>Q. Had the prisoner then any person he called his wife?</p>
               <p>Day. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. What was her name?</p>
               <p>Day. She was called 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person410">
                  Anne 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person410" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person410" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person410" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             before he married her.</p>
               <p>Pris. Co. Is 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person411">
                  Anne 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person411" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person411" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person411" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             living now?</p>
               <p>Day. Yes; I saw her about nine o'clock this morning; they had a child when they were at my house, but she was not born there.</p>
               <p>Q. What Name was the child called by?</p>
               <p>Day. 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person412">
                  Sarah 
                  Chevin 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person412" type="surname" value="Chevin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person412" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person412" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>The Revd . Mr. 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person413">
                  Charles 
                  Bellinger 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person413" type="surname" value="Bellinger"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person413" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person413" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 25th of November 1747, I married 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person414">
                  Robert 
                  Chevin 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person414" type="surname" value="Chevin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person414" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             to 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person415">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Atwood 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person415" type="surname" value="Atwood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person415" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person415" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             of <placeName id="t17480907-52-crimeloc270">St. Michael Cornhill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17480907-52-crimeloc270" type="placeName" value="St. Michael Cornhill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17480907-52-crimeloc270" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480907-52-off267 t17480907-52-crimeloc270"></join>, spinster, at the parish of <placeName id="t17480907-52-crimeloc271">Trinity Minories</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17480907-52-crimeloc271" type="placeName" value="Trinity Minories"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17480907-52-crimeloc271" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480907-52-off267 t17480907-52-crimeloc271"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17480907-52-person416">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Atwood 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person416" type="surname" value="Atwood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person416" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person416" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>Q. Was you at any time married to any body ?</p>
               <p>Atwood . I was married the 25th of November last in the Minories to the prisoner, and lived with him about five or six months.</p>
               <p>Q. How came you not to live with him longer?</p>
               <p>Atwood. Because I heard he had another wife, and then I left him; but he all along told me that he was a batchelor .</p>
               <p>Prisoner. She did not leave me upon that footing , it was upon another.</p>
               <p>Ann Vink. I took the prisoner at my house at the Red Cross in the Minories, in the liberty of the City of London.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. My Lord, I will clear myself of this indictment; for I was not married to 
               <persName id="t17480907-52-person417">
                  Anne 
                  Towns 
               <interp inst="t17480907-52-person417" type="surname" value="Towns"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person417" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-person417" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Q. Have you any Witnesses ?</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I have not; I am not provided with any; I have been ill of a fever, and was almost out of my senses .</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17480907-52-verdict272" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-verdict272" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17480907-52-punish273" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-punish273" type="punishmentCategory" value="miscPunish"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17480907-52-punish273" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="branding"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480907-52-defend397 t17480907-52-punish273"></join>
               
                     <note>[Branding. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
